-- Italian Stocks: Bulgari, ERG and Geox Shares Are Active in Milan Trading
-- B y   A d a m   E w i n g
-- 2010-11-12T17:13:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/atlantia-telecom-italia-bulgari-fiat-may-move-italian-equity-preview.html
The benchmark  FTSE MIB Index  dropped
26.13, or 0.1 percent, to 20,829.83 at the 5:30 p.m. close in
Milan. The gauge has fallen 1.7 percent this week.  The following companies were active.  Bulgari SpA  (BUL IM) tumbled 4.8 percent to 7.10 euros, the
biggest drop in eight months. The world’s third-largest jeweler
said third-quarter net income was 16.6 million euros ($22.8
million), trailing the 19.8 million euros average analyst
estimate in a Bloomberg survey. Bulgari was also cut to
“underweight” from “neutral” at JPMorgan Chase & Co.  ERG SpA  (ERG IM) slipped 1.6 percent to 9.69 euros, the
lowest close in more than a month. The refiner swung to a loss
of 13.9 million euros in the third quarter from a profit of 5.2
million euros a year earlier, according to a statement
distributed by the Italian exchange.  Geox SpA  (GEO IM) decreased for the fourth day, sliding 8.3
percent to 3.75 euros. The shoemaker said nine-month net income
fell to 72.4 million euros from 89.7 million euros a year
earlier, according to a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Adam Ewing  in Stockholm at 
 aewing5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
